         <div type="transcription">
            <p>
<lb corresp="#a1"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><gap reason="plain" unit="part"/>ä</w><w>lwā</w><w>tspoki<supplied>ñc-äṃ</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#a2"/><gap reason="lost"/><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><w>tmaṃ</w><w>tmaṃnäk</w><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#a3"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>tsru</w><w>yärmann</w><w>a<supplied>ts</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#a4"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>t</w><w>cami</w><w>ṣoṅkā<supplied>tsāñ</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#a5"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>t</supplied>pr<supplied>e</supplied>näk</w><w>smā<supplied>lok</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#a6"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>ṣäṃ</w><pc>:</pc><num value="3">3</num><w>mäṃ</w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b1"/><gap reason="lost"/><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><w>tär</w><w>säm</w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b2"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>tär</w><pc>:</pc><num value="4">4</num><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b3"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>ṣ</w><w>ṣoṅkātsāñ</w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b4"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>lyutār</supplied></w><w><supplied>me</supplied>maṣ</w><w>lālaṃṣkeṃ</w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b5"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>ṣiṃñc-äṃ</w><w>puk</w><w>kapśa<supplied>ñi</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b6"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><gap reason="plain" unit="part"/>aṃ</w><w>tsäknäṣtr-änn</w><w>o<supplied>ki</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/></p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the animals devour (?) (him) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... there [and] there ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... in small measure ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... his ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... so a liar ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... 3. ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... he ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... this extraordinarily tender ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... they ... him ... all [his] body ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... burns as it were ...</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="remarks">Upper and lower margins are preserved.</note><note corresp="#a1" type="philcomment">: cf. <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a152"/> b6 <hi>lwā tspokinc-äṃ</hi>. The meaning 'enjoy' (<bibl><title corresp="ref:malzahn2010"/><citedRange>999</citedRange></bibl>) is based on the etymological connection with <hi>tspok</hi> 'taste' and does not follow from the passages where the verb is attested.</note><note corresp="#a4 #b3" type="philcomment">: cf. <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a166"/> b5 <hi>cami ṣoṅkātsāśśi</hi>. This word may suggest appurtenance to the Garbhasūtra.</note><note corresp="#a5" type="philcomment"><hi>smā(lok)</hi>: Possibly a trace of the upper part of the <hi>l</hi>-ligature is seen to the right. This restoration is due to Ilya Itkin (p.c. 8 September 2016).</note><note corresp="#b2" type="philcomment"><hi>4</hi>: This reading, which confirms the order of recto and verso, is due to Ilya Itkin (p.c. 8 September 2016).</note><note corresp="#b3" type="philcomment"><hi>ṣoṅkātsāñ</hi>: This reading, instead of <hi>ṣoṅkātsāś(śi)</hi>, is due to Ilya Itkin (p.c. 8 September 2016).</note><note corresp="#b4" type="philcomment">: See <bibl><title corresp="ref:itkin2016"/><citedRange>72</citedRange></bibl>.</note><note corresp="#b5" type="philcomment"><hi>/// ṣiṃñc-äṃ</hi>: possibly <hi>(klyo)ṣiṃñc-äṃ</hi> 'may they hear him'.</note><note corresp="#b6" type="philcomment"><hi>tsäknäṣtr-änn o(ki)</hi>: This reading, instead of <hi>tsäknäṣtr-än no(ṣ)</hi>, is due to Sergey Malyshev (p.c. 8 September 2016).</note></p>
         </div>
